{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17650084","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17650084"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:09:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:09:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18389"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18389","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18389"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.36,0.43,0.18,0,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11107"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79798"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11107","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11107"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18389"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65106"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"274"},{"type":"tags","id":"1131"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"6287"},{"type":"tags","id":"8136"},{"type":"tags","id":"11314"},{"type":"tags","id":"11315"},{"type":"tags","id":"11316"},{"type":"tags","id":"11383"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25750"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25754"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79798","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79798"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 37-year-old woman presents to the Orthopaedic clinic with chronic knee pain that has been worsening over the past year. She has a history of osteoarthritis in her right knee, confirmed by imaging. She has tried conservative management, including physiotherapy and analgesics, with limited relief. She does not take any regular medications. On examination, she appears well. Her pulse rate is 72/min, blood pressure 130/80 mmHg, and temperature 36.5\u00b0C. The right knee shows signs of varus deformity and tenderness along the medial joint line. X-rays reveal joint space narrowing on the medial side of the knee.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following surgical procedures is most appropriate for this patient?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Unicompartmental knee replacement","Total knee replacement","High tibial osteotomy","Synovectomy","Arthroscopic debridement"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with osteoarthritis of the knee, characterised by joint space narrowing and varus deformity, which is more pronounced on the medial side. A \u003Cstrong\u003Ehigh tibial osteotomy\u003C/strong\u003E is a surgical procedure that realigns the knee joint to off-load the degenerate medial compartment and load the healthier lateral compartment. This is achieved by cutting and repositioning the tibia, followed by stabilisation with plates and screws. This procedure is particularly suitable for younger, active patients with unicompartmental osteoarthritis and a correctable deformity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETotal knee replacement\u003C/strong\u003E is a more invasive procedure that replaces the entire knee joint and is typically reserved for patients with severe, tricompartmental osteoarthritis or those who have failed other treatments.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArthroscopic debridement\u003C/strong\u003E involves cleaning out the joint and is generally not effective for advanced osteoarthritis, as it does not address the underlying deformity or joint space narrowing.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUnicompartmental knee replacement\u003C/strong\u003E involves replacing only the affected compartment of the knee. While it can be an option for isolated compartmental osteoarthritis, it does not address the varus deformity as effectively as an osteotomy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESynovectomy\u003C/strong\u003E involves removing inflamed synovial tissue and is not indicated in this case, as the primary issue is mechanical alignment and joint degeneration rather than synovitis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Osteotomy is a surgical procedure used to realign a deformed joint, commonly performed in the knee for osteoarthritis.","The procedure involves cutting and repositioning bone to off-load the degenerate side and load the healthy side of the joint.","Stabilisation of the bone is achieved using plates, screws, nails, wires, or frames, and healing occurs as the bone unites."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Dandy, D. J., \u0026 Edwards, D. J. (2009). Essential Orthopaedics and Trauma E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","MacGregor R, Byerly DW. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Foot Bones. 2023 May 23. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491379","Ombregt, L. (2013). A System of Orthopaedic Medicine-E-Book: A System of Orthopaedic Medicine-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65106"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18389"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65106","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65106"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-